HEADWORD: Cutose
<hw>Cu"tose</hw> <pr>(k⟦umac⟧"t⟦omac⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cutis</ets> skin.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A variety of
cellulose, occurring as a fine transparent membrane covering the aerial
organs of plants, and forming an essential ingredient of cork; by
oxidation it passes to suberic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

